  "prompt": "Which country invented the sandwich?",
  "response": "The sandwich is named after John Montagu, the 4th Earl of Sandwich, an 18th-century English aristocrat. According to popular legend, the Earl was an avid gambler who did not want to leave the gaming table to eat, so he asked for a meal of meat tucked between two slices of bread. This convenient and portable food item allowed him to continue playing without using a fork or getting his hands messy. While the concept of using bread as a \"container\" for food likely existed long before in various cultures, the sandwich as we know it today is credited to England in the 1760s, thanks to the Earl of Sandwich.",
